author: Jack Power
title: Coronavirus: Around 11,000 people awaiting test results, HSE chief says
description: Increased testing capacity will be key to any decision to reduce economic and social restrictions
content:
The States coronavirus testing backlog has been reduced from a high point of around 35,000 people waiting for results to some 11,000, Health Service Executive (HSE) chief executive Paul Reid has said.
